10:25.959 --> 10:27.425
Okay.

10:27.427 --> 10:29.427
Um, my brother will be back
in one minute.

10:29.429 --> 10:31.396
Will you hold this spot
for me?

10:31.398 --> 10:32.297
Hmm!

10:32.299 --> 10:34.065
Is that a yes?
Hmm!

10:34.067 --> 10:35.834
What is that?
Hmm!

10:35.836 --> 10:37.836
Just save
our damn place!
Hmm!

10:37.838 --> 10:39.871
All right. If you
come to your feet,
go for the takedown.

10:39.873 --> 10:41.906
Don't let him
get away with that!
More explosion there!

10:41.908 --> 10:44.075
Whoa, what are you doing?
What are you doing?
What?

10:44.077 --> 10:45.243
What are you doing
with the folding chair?

10:45.245 --> 10:46.911
You said to practice
our takedowns.

10:46.913 --> 10:49.447
The chair-bash is my
character's patented move.

10:49.449 --> 10:50.482
Your character?

10:50.484 --> 10:52.550
Yeah. For the wwf.

10:52.552 --> 10:53.585
They call me goldberg.

10:53.587 --> 10:56.287
My backstory is my parents
gave me up for adoption,

10:56.289 --> 10:58.823
And then I grew up on the
rough streets of philly.

10:58.825 --> 11:00.191
I'm sensitive,
so ladies love me,

11:00.193 --> 11:03.361
But I also have a raging side,
so men can relate, too.

11:03.363 --> 11:04.796
But this isn't the wwf.

11:04.798 --> 11:06.297
And as someone
whose parents really did

11:06.299 --> 11:08.133
Give him up for adoption,
I can promise you

11:08.135 --> 11:11.102
It's a lot more emotionally
complicated than that.

11:11.104 --> 11:11.970
Now,
put the chair back.

11:11.972 --> 11:14.372
Adult adam:
<i>While barry was having</i>
<i>a tough time</i>

11:14.374 --> 11:15.740
<i>Accepting this wasn't the wwf,</i>

11:15.742 --> 11:19.444
<i>He was having an even</i>
<i>tougher time learning</i> annie.

11:19.446 --> 11:21.980
<i>♪ together at last</i>

11:22.581 --> 11:25.583
<i>♪ together forever</i>

11:25.818 --> 11:27.886
<i>♪ we're tying a knot</i>

11:27.888 --> 11:29.254
What's that, murray?

11:29.256 --> 11:32.223
<i>♪ they never can sever</i>

11:32.425 --> 11:35.126
<i>♪ I don't need</i>
<i>sunshine now</i>

11:35.128 --> 11:37.629
<i>♪ to turn my gray skies blue</i>

11:37.631 --> 11:39.531
<i>♪ sing it</i>
<i>from the diaphragm</i>

11:39.533 --> 11:43.468
<i>♪ I don't need anything</i>
<i>but you ♪</i>

11:43.470 --> 11:45.103
Ahh! Aha!

11:45.105 --> 11:48.540
I'm kind of wondering if
this whole thing is worth it.

11:48.542 --> 11:49.240
It is what it is.

11:49.242 --> 11:51.142
Adult adam:
<i>Pops and my dad</i>
<i>had helped barry</i>

11:51.144 --> 11:52.410
<i>Pull off</i>
<i>the perfect cover story.</i>

11:52.412 --> 11:55.780
<i>Unfortunately, erica wasn't</i>
<i>interested in covering for me.</i>

11:55.782 --> 11:57.048
Hey, that's my spot.

11:57.050 --> 11:58.783
My sister was saving it
for me.

11:58.785 --> 11:59.417
Where did she go?

11:59.419 --> 12:01.486
Like I care
what your sister would do.

12:01.488 --> 12:04.389
She went to get a cheesesteak
with her smoking-hot friend.

12:04.391 --> 12:04.989
Come on.

12:04.991 --> 12:06.691
I just went to the bathroom
for like 10 seconds.

12:06.693 --> 12:08.927
Sorry, man. But you should
have planned ahead.

12:08.929 --> 12:10.829
The smart ones of us
brought along someone

12:10.831 --> 12:13.298
We could trust
to hold our spot in line.

12:13.300 --> 12:14.966
Others
in more unwieldy costumes

12:14.968 --> 12:17.168
Have rigged themselves
with elaborate tubing

12:17.170 --> 12:18.136
And disposable
plastic bags

12:18.138 --> 12:20.105
So that they might quietly
relieve themselves

12:20.107 --> 12:22.240
Even while talking to
a stranger.

12:22.242 --> 12:23.975
Ahh.

12:24.810 --> 12:25.376
What?

12:25.378 --> 12:27.445
Can't a man "ahh" in relief
without being judged?

12:27.447 --> 12:30.115
Unreal.
Unreal, you guys.

12:30.117 --> 12:30.615
Seriously?

12:30.617 --> 12:32.417
You're not gonna
let me back into my spot?

12:32.419 --> 12:33.651
I'm just a boy.

12:33.653 --> 12:34.152
Seriously?

12:34.154 --> 12:36.554
Luke skywalker
was just a boy, okay?

12:36.556 --> 12:37.655
Rules are the rules.

12:37.657 --> 12:40.692
Good luck
catching the Sunday matinee.

12:40.694 --> 12:43.495
Adult adam:  <i>My sister</i>
<i>had done the unthinkable.</i>

12:43.497 --> 12:45.163
<i>She ruined</i> star wars.

12:45.165 --> 12:48.533
You're on the mat
sizing up your opponent.

12:48.535 --> 12:49.834
The ref
blows the whistle.

12:49.836 --> 12:52.036
He makes his move.
What do you do?

12:52.038 --> 12:53.605
I bounce off the ropes
to get momentum,

12:53.607 --> 12:54.973
And I spear him
with my body.

12:54.975 --> 12:57.342
Again!
It's not that kind of wres...

12:57.344 --> 13:00.411
I know, it's not
that type of wrestling.

13:00.413 --> 13:00.912
I get it.

13:00.914 --> 13:03.181
But those
are the only moves I perfected

13:03.183 --> 13:04.082
On my bed jumping around.

13:04.084 --> 13:07.051
It's true. I've seen him.
He's quite a jumper, this one.

13:07.053 --> 13:09.053
Okay, let me show you
a real move.

13:09.055 --> 13:11.122
This was my specialty
back in the day.

13:11.124 --> 13:14.926
You use your opponent's weight
and strength against him.

13:14.928 --> 13:16.227
You smell like sandwich.

13:16.229 --> 13:16.828
Shut up.

13:16.830 --> 13:19.364
As I lean in to you,
you pull back

13:19.366 --> 13:22.767
And use your opponent's
momentum to take him down!

13:22.769 --> 13:24.803
Oh, my god.
I'm so bored right now.

13:24.805 --> 13:27.238
Just let me hit you
with something!

13:27.240 --> 13:28.540
Pops, get me a 2x4.

13:28.542 --> 13:31.309
What are you doing?
No 2x4s! I told you!

13:31.311 --> 13:34.279
Beverly:
Barry norman goldberg,
look at me.

13:34.281 --> 13:36.981
Are you
on the wrestling team?

13:36.983 --> 13:38.783
Uh...No?

13:38.785 --> 13:39.450
Oh, really?

13:39.452 --> 13:41.286
Because I was just down
at the school theater

13:41.288 --> 13:42.587
Building an orphanage
for a show

13:42.589 --> 13:44.055
That apparently
you're not even in.

13:44.057 --> 13:47.091
What? You promised you weren't
going down there.

13:47.093 --> 13:48.293
I have a problem.

13:48.295 --> 13:50.595
Yes, he's on
the wrestling team,

13:50.597 --> 13:51.663
But that's a good thing.

13:51.665 --> 13:53.264
I was on the wrestling team,

13:53.266 --> 13:55.433
And look how fine
I turned out.

13:55.435 --> 13:59.204
(laughing) ohhhhwha!

13:59.672 --> 14:01.606
(laughing)

14:03.442 --> 14:06.244
How dare you
go behind my back

14:06.246 --> 14:10.014
And encourage my delicious
baby muffin to lie to me!

14:10.016 --> 14:13.218
Bev, come on.
It's not that big of a deal.

14:13.220 --> 14:14.018
Let the boy wrestle.

14:14.020 --> 14:16.721
Helen cutler's son
was in a wrestling match once

14:16.723 --> 14:18.156
And his head
popped right off

14:18.158 --> 14:20.258
And now he lives his life
as just a head.

14:20.260 --> 14:23.094
There's no such thing
as just a head!

14:23.096 --> 14:24.362
You need organs to live.

14:24.364 --> 14:25.663
Well,
tell that to helen cutler

14:25.665 --> 14:28.199
As she's carrying her son
around the grocery store

14:28.201 --> 14:28.933
Like a football.

14:28.935 --> 14:31.970
Well, where's his heart?
You need a heart to function!

14:31.972 --> 14:32.604
It's in his neck.

14:32.606 --> 14:34.873
He's got a little neck
with organs in it.

14:34.875 --> 14:37.008
Oh, so now
he's got a neck!

14:37.010 --> 14:38.443
What else has he got?

14:38.445 --> 14:39.477
Maybe a body?

14:39.479 --> 14:40.612
Everyone, shut up!

14:40.614 --> 14:44.382
All my life, you've been
treating me like a baby.

14:44.384 --> 14:46.417
Well, guess what,
it stops now.

14:46.419 --> 14:49.354
I'm a grown adult man
and I'm gonna wrestle

14:49.356 --> 14:52.357
And there's nothing
you can do about it!

14:52.359 --> 14:52.824
Nothing!

14:52.826 --> 14:56.227
Adult adam:  <i>Despite</i>
<i>my brother's goofy run,</i>
<i>he'd made up his mind.</i>

14:56.229 --> 14:56.895
<i>It was go time,</i>

14:56.897 --> 15:00.198
<i>But barry wasn't the only one</i>
<i>ready for a fight.</i>

15:00.200 --> 15:02.734
There you are!
You scared me to death!

15:02.736 --> 15:04.035
Where were you?

15:04.037 --> 15:05.003
Where were you?

15:05.005 --> 15:07.872
I asked you to do one thing,
stand!

15:07.874 --> 15:09.173
Just stand there!

15:09.175 --> 15:10.375
But you couldn't even
do that!

15:10.377 --> 15:13.011
And now I'll never see
<i>return of the jedi.</i>

15:13.013 --> 15:14.879
Oh, please,
just to spite me?

15:14.881 --> 15:17.348
Correct!
You ruined  <i>star wars</i> for me.

15:17.350 --> 15:20.652
From this point on, I'll
have nothing to do with it.

15:20.654 --> 15:22.353
Nothing!

15:26.525 --> 15:29.460
Dang it!
That's a collector's item!

15:29.462 --> 15:31.963
But I don't care!
(breathing heavily)

15:31.965 --> 15:32.597
Why did I do this?

15:32.599 --> 15:34.198
You made me lose control
of my body.

15:34.200 --> 15:35.967
You honestly want to know
why I left?

15:35.969 --> 15:38.369
I didn't want my friends
to see me stand in line

15:38.371 --> 15:41.239
At some space movie
that I got blackmailed into

15:41.241 --> 15:42.173
By my dumb kid brother.

15:42.175 --> 15:44.208
I blackmailed you
because it's the only way

15:44.210 --> 15:47.011
To get you to spend time
with me.

15:47.112 --> 15:50.782
And I didn't used to just be
your dumb kid brother.

15:50.784 --> 15:53.551
I used to be your friend.

15:59.058 --> 16:00.158
Adult adam:
<i>It had been a full day</i>

16:00.160 --> 16:02.460
<i>Since I banished</i> star wars
<i>from my life.</i>

16:02.462 --> 16:04.295
<i>I was in a sarlacc pit</i>
<i>of despair,</i>

16:04.297 --> 16:07.565
<i>That is, until a certain</i>
<i>princess rescued me.</i>

16:07.567 --> 16:09.834
Hey!
Get up. Put this on.

16:09.836 --> 16:10.735
We're going
to that movie.

16:10.737 --> 16:12.670
I told you I'm not seeing
the Sunday matinee.

16:12.672 --> 16:15.306
It's like wearing
somebody else's wedding dress.

16:15.308 --> 16:16.741
What does that even mean?

16:16.743 --> 16:19.844
It doesn't matter.
We're going today.

16:19.846 --> 16:20.378
How?

16:20.380 --> 16:22.747
Well, I told the theater
manager what happened,

16:22.749 --> 16:24.415
And he was
incredibly sympathetic.

16:24.417 --> 16:25.717
He's gonna sneak us in.
Really?

16:25.719 --> 16:29.454
I also said I would
go to dinner with him
and his grandparents.

16:29.456 --> 16:31.556
I really wish I would have
just stayed in line.

16:31.558 --> 16:33.491
Adult adam:  <i>Meanwhile,</i>
<i>my brother was ready to fight.</i>

16:33.493 --> 16:36.361
<i>And according to barry logic,</i>
<i>if he won this match,</i>

16:36.363 --> 16:37.462
<i>Lexy would never forget</i>
<i>his name.</i>

16:37.464 --> 16:39.464
<i>And even though</i>
<i>he had a lot to lose,</i>

16:39.466 --> 16:41.966
<i>It was my dad</i>
<i>who had the butterflies.</i>

16:41.968 --> 16:43.901
How you doing, champ?
You nervous?

16:43.903 --> 16:46.170
I'm not nervous.
Don't be nervous.

16:46.172 --> 16:48.973
Uh, I'm a little nervous,
not about the wrestling thing.

16:48.975 --> 16:50.408
I'm just worried
about my catchphrase

16:50.410 --> 16:52.877
'cause once I say it,
I can never take it back.

16:52.879 --> 16:55.046
I was thinking,
"welcome to the mat."

16:55.048 --> 16:55.646
No catchphrase.

16:55.648 --> 16:56.981
Goldberg,
quit trading recipes.

16:56.983 --> 16:59.317
Let's go! You're up!
Let's go, let's go!

16:59.319 --> 17:00.118
Look alive! Come on!

17:00.120 --> 17:03.588
(europe's  <i>the final countdown</i>
<i>plays)</i>

17:03.590 --> 17:04.856
Adult adam:
<i>This was it,</i>

17:04.858 --> 17:07.258
<i>The start of</i>
<i>my brother's wrestling career,</i>

17:07.260 --> 17:09.794
<i>And nothing was</i>
<i>gonna stop him.</i>

17:12.097 --> 17:14.665
I said no!

17:14.667 --> 17:15.666
Mom?

17:15.668 --> 17:17.668
Are you kidding me right now?
Move.

17:17.670 --> 17:20.571
I will not move.
I will never move.

17:20.573 --> 17:21.572
You're my special boy.

17:21.574 --> 17:23.174
If you end up
being just a head,

17:23.176 --> 17:25.176
Then I have failed
as a mother.

17:25.178 --> 17:26.644
No.

17:26.646 --> 17:27.445
No.

17:27.447 --> 17:29.313
Barry!
What did I say?

17:29.315 --> 17:31.182
What did I say?
What did, ohh!

17:31.184 --> 17:31.816
(crowd gasps)

17:31.818 --> 17:34.452
Mom, lexy bloom
